Package ohos.rpc

Interface IRemoteObject

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InstallerCallback, LocalRemoteObject, NfcController.ReaderModeCallbackStub, OnPermissionChangedCallback, RemoteObject, RemoteProxy

    public interface IRemoteObject
    A remote object interface that must be implemented by service providers and users.

    This interface can be used to query or obtain an interface descriptor, add or remove a death notification, dump object status to a specific file, and send messages.

    Since:
    1

    • Method Detail

      • queryLocalInterface

        IRemoteBroker queryLocalInterface​(String descriptor)
        Queries the description of an interface.

        A valid IRemoteBroker object is returned for an interface used by the service provider; null is returned for an interface used by the service user, indicating that the interface is not a local one.

        Parameters:
        descriptor - Indicates a string of the interface descriptor.
        Returns:
        Returns the IRemoteBroker object bound to the specified interface descriptor.
        Since:
        1

      • sendRequest

        boolean sendRequest​(int code,
                    MessageParcel data,
                    MessageParcel reply,
                    MessageOption option)
             throws RemoteException
        Sends a MessageParcel message to the peer process in synchronous or asynchronous mode.

        If asynchronous mode is set for option, a response is returned immediately. If synchronous mode is set for option, the interface will wait for a response from the peer process until the request times out. The user must prepare reply for receiving the execution result given by the peer process.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the message code, which is determined by both sides of the communication. If the interface is generated by the IDL tool, the message code is automatically generated by IDL.
        data - Indicates the MessageParcel object sent to the peer process.
        reply - Indicates the MessageParcel object returned by the peer process.
        option - Indicates the synchronous or asynchronous mode to send messages.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the method is called successfully; returns false otherwise.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - Throws this exception if the method fails to be called.
        Since:
        1

      • addDeathRecipient

        boolean addDeathRecipient​(IRemoteObject.DeathRecipient recipient,
                          int flags)
        Registers a callback used to receive notifications of the death of a remote object.

        This method is called if the remote object process matching the RemoteProxy object dies.

        Parameters:
        recipient - Indicates the callback to be registered.
        flags - Indicates the flag of the death notification.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the callback is registered successfully; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        1

        void slowPathDump​(FileDescriptor fd,

           throws RemoteException

        This method applies only to data dump on the same device.

        Parameters:
        fd - Indicates the file descriptor of the target file.
        args - Indicates the arguments (an array of strings) to dump.
